# DefComm Workflow Flowchart

Below is a visual representation of the secure communication pipeline, from registration to recipient decryption.

```mermaid
graph TD
    %% Define Styles
    classDef hq fill:#f96,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px;
    classDef secure fill:#bbf,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px;
    classDef storage fill:#dfd,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px;

    %% Workflow Steps
    A([1. Operative Registration]) --> B{2. HQ Approval};
    B -- Denied --> C[Access Blocked];
    B -- Approved --> D[3. Client AES-256 Encryption];
    
    D --> E[4. Secure HTTPS Transmission];
    E --> F[(5. MySQL Encrypted Storage)];
    
    F --> G[6. Real-time Threat Scanning];
    G --> H([7. HQ Dashboard Alert]);
    
    G --> I[8. Recipient Fetches & Decrypts];

    %% Applying Styles
    class B,H hq;
    class D,E,I secure;
    class F storage;
```

---

## How to Read This Diagram
- **Orange Nodes**: Represent **HQ Governance** and administrative control points.
- **Blue Nodes**: Represent **Security Operations** handled on the client-side/transmission layer.
- **Green Node**: Represents the **State of Data** (Zero-Knowledge persistence in the database).
- **Arrows**: Show the logical progression of a message from the sender to the command dashboard and the final recipient.
